    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Feature description\n\nIt would be great to have the possibility to supply a `side` argument to the `resize` command.\r\nE.g. `resize left +10` which would increase the left side of the buffer. If the buffer is already on the left side, nothing should happen.\r\nThis would allow for nicer resize mappings, where the buffer size could be increased with `h,j,k,l` and decreased with `H,J,K,L` for example.",
